subject: Disabled IPv6 privacy extensions
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-08-17 03:05:59.000000000', 'files': ['devstack-vm-gate.sh'], 'message': 'Disabled IPv6 privacy extensions

The IPv6 privacy extensions can cause issues by perfering a private network
over a pulbic which may limit connectivity in certain situations. An example
of a connectivity issue can be seen by trusty images not being able to
run a traceroute6 to "git.openstack.org". To resolve this issue the RFC3041
extensions have been disabled by default.

Change-Id: Ifcedc69597a61c350cba8247baa01541aa38c9f5
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>
'}]
commit_message:
Disabled IPv6 privacy extensions

The IPv6 privacy extensions can cause issues by perfering a private network
over a pulbic which may limit connectivity in certain situations. An example
of a connectivity issue can be seen by trusty images not being able to
run a traceroute6 to "git.openstack.org". To resolve this issue the RFC3041
extensions have been disabled by default.

Change-Id: Ifcedc69597a61c350cba8247baa01541aa38c9f5
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>

commit_message:
Fix service filtering when claiming clusters

The health manager is not claiming clusters accurately when service is
restarted. The reason is that there are some dead service records to be
removed next time one of the engines gets restarted. This patch adds a
check about the service's status and filters the service records based
on the check result.

Change-Id: Id482e74068cc1cb4394c79f14f1c6442cf9f717b
Partial-Bug: #1613552

subject: HAHT - Mitigate missed action during DSD failover
revisions:
[{'number': 4, 'created': '2016-08-16 21:11:31.000000000', 'files': ['congress/common/config.py', 'congress/tests/api/test_datasource_model.py', 'congress/api/datasource_model.py', 'congress/dse2/data_service.py', 'congress/policy_engines/agnostic.py', 'congress/dse2/dse_node.py'], 'message': 'HAHT - Mitigate missed action during DSD failover

Added option to retry execute action to mitigate missed actions in
case of DSD failover or transport failures.

Also changed action execution to be asynchronous so that PE can
continue to operate while waiting for action execution to finish
This seems to be a good idea even without retry because depending
on the action, execution could take minutes, preventing the PE from
responding to new data/requests if done synchronously. Some tempest
tests may need updating for change to asynchronous.

New config options:
- execute_action_retry to enable retry
- execute_action_retry_timeout to set timeout until giving up

Closes-Bug: 1600013
Partially implements blueprint: high-availability-design

Change-Id: I782118d2d3b683ae979b8748935a1bd8b7bc99dd
'}]
commit_message:
HAHT - Mitigate missed action during DSD failover

Added option to retry execute action to mitigate missed actions in
case of DSD failover or transport failures.

Also changed action execution to be asynchronous so that PE can
continue to operate while waiting for action execution to finish
This seems to be a good idea even without retry because depending
on the action, execution could take minutes, preventing the PE from
responding to new data/requests if done synchronously. Some tempest
tests may need updating for change to asynchronous.

New config options:
- execute_action_retry to enable retry
- execute_action_retry_timeout to set timeout until giving up

Closes-Bug: 1600013
Partially implements blueprint: high-availability-design

Change-Id: I782118d2d3b683ae979b8748935a1bd8b7bc99dd

commit_message:
Introduce support for kvm acceleration

This change introduces kvm acceleration support. The default settings
still use qemu as the domain type and kvm needs to be explicitly set
in order to enable it.

Change-Id: I59af1b7a844b927cac45722f7ea7ea4abeef7c8f
Signed-off-by: Fatih Degirmenci <fatih.degirmenci@ericsson.com>

commit_message:
Replication, hard-coding and dict.name issues in K2

Replication was tested with self-replication due to unavailability
of K2 arrays. Source and target K2 arrays were same.
_delete_volume_replica and _get_replica_status are not working with
different source and target K2 arrays while testing replication.

Hard-coded value of RPO(500) is raising exception while retype:
rpo must be either 1 min or multiple of 5 min

vol_type.name is raising below exception:
AttributeError: 'dict' object has no attribute 'name'

Change-Id: I86e840f9fbc886ef661ddf1de77d433adb901ae5
Closes-Bug: #1612602
Co-Authored-By: VenkataKrishna Reddy <Venkata.Krishna.ctr@kaminario.com>

commit_message:
Initialize 'auth' to empty dict on bifrost_configdrives_dynamic

The bifrost-configdrives-dynamic role invocation fails at
the update_facts_from_ironic include, due to initializing the
'auth' fact to None.
Ansible converts None to 'None', but then the openstack argument
spec expects to be a dict, which fails as it cannot convert it.
Setting this to an empty dict fixes the issue.

Change-Id: Ia807db74b6a2f0cc107216270f8538232019c607
Closes-Bug: LP1612586

commit_message:
Add missing ICMP option for pxc & mariadb

An option called "icmp" was added to cfg.py to allow for the
ICMP protocol to be added to the security group created by
task manager. The option was added to all datastores except
MariaDB and PXC. This commit corrects that and adds the option
for those 2 datastores.

Change-Id: Icd2845cf689fecb7bda18046061b601b3ee123ed
Closes-bug: 1613768

commit_message:
Add facility to write fallback resolvers on OpenStack hosts

This change adds the ability for the openstack_hosts role to
add resolvers from a list of fall back resolvers to the host
machine's resolv files should an nslookup on localhost fail.
The change will give deployers the ability to correct / ensure
DNS is functional on a given host machine.

Change-Id: Icc044f483087f809150d7fff2b183397ec95c5ee
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>

commit_message:
Allow bound ports to be trunked if the driver can support it

Some drivers, like the Open vSwitch one, may restrict the creation of a
trunk from a bound port (i.e. prevents from creating trunks after a VM
is already booted on the port).

This limitation frees us from worrying about dataplane migrations for OVS
as trunk ports and regular ports are wired differently.

However, other drivers, like the Linux Bridge one, may not be affected by
this limitation, and the existing rule should be relaxed to allow the
operation based on whether not the driver can support it.

Partially-implements: blueprint vlan-aware-vms

Change-Id: Ia938eb7cc845f6f144924acdb0e333d23516fcca

commit_message:
Fix neutron security group tests for 5.1.0 neutronclient

python-neutronclient 5.1.0 has a different API call for
find_resourceid_by_name_or_id now:

84c42160e9eac654e734a19032237fdf1a8cb058

That breaks the neutron security group driver unit tests
which are relying on a mocked out version of the neutronclient
which itself is a bad idea but not completely re-written here

This blocks getting to use neutronclient 5.1.0 in
upper-constraints so this change just fixes the immediate
breakage.

Also removes test_get_raises_no_unique_match_error which
duplicates the coverage from test_associate_duplicate_names
for the 409 scenario.

Change-Id: Iee340361bc656a0bd3a246e02de41a8f4f89bebf
Closes-Bug: #1612494

commit_message:
Trust controller refactoring

In lieu of new more complicated role system role collections tend to grow,
so extracting all roles to normalize/populate trust scope should be more
granular. This patch is a rework of role treating logic in trust controller.

commit_message:
Toggle Live Search

A simple play/pause button to toggling live search results.

Notice the play/pause button next to the search results. When
paused, modified items are marked as "dirty", but will not
auto-update unless the user's current search is live.

Partially-Implements: blueprint edit-live-data
Change-Id: Ib6fee5d07c4943a1827f04e6aeedb4904cf663d1

commit_message:
Remove *openstack/common* from flake8 excclude list in tox.ini

The *openstack/common* was used to keep codes from oslo-incubator,
but oslo-incubator was ignore in oslo3.11.0. So I think we
needn't use it any more.
Here is the oslo.utils CHANGES link:
http://docs.openstack.org/developer/oslo.utils/history.html

Change-Id: Ia8f46f8192bed49a7a7d71103c45a6ca5d2f6012

commit_message:
Add RouterPort bindings for all HA ports

Adding these bindings allows us to remove the special-cased HA
interface deletion in l3_hamode_db that had the potential for
leaving orphaned ports on failures. With the bindings present,
the interface deletion is handled before the router delete so
a failure to delete the interface will prevent router deletion.

Related-Bug: #1540271
Change-Id: I2de8503742661c18a2ec2c5ade7ec58ea380e749

commit_message:
Add a unique hit identifier to search results

Searchlight _id is only unique within a given _type. In order to have
unique IDs for searchlight hits, the UI must currently use
_id + _type. This patch adds that as an "id" on  incoming search results.

This "id" is for UI internal use and is not usable for calls back to
searchlight API.

Partially-Implements: blueprint edit-live-data
Change-Id: I8c9b2ef09039336f56bdf44167bcdfbaac5fc950

commit_message:
Use tempest.lib instead of tempest-lib

tempest-lib is marked as deprecated now.
The library is not maintained and Tempest itself provides the stable
interfaces under tempest.lib as [1] said.
So this patch makes the project use tempest.lib for long-term maintenance.

[1]: https://github.com/openstack/tempest-lib/blob/master/README.rst#tempest-lib

Change-Id: I78beb25bba797cf463626c32c6cb6ebb1760b8e4

revisions:
[{'number': 4, 'created': '2016-08-16 08:19:51.000000000', 'files': ['nova/conf/libvirt.py', 'releasenotes/notes/libvirt-change-default-value-of-live-migration-tunnelled-4248cf76df605fdf.yaml', 'nova/tests/unit/virt/libvirt/test_driver.py'], 'message': 'Change default value of live_migration_tunnelled to False

Given the impact of libvirt tunnelling mechanism this patch changes
default value of live_migration_tunnelled to False. There are few
reasons to do that:
* Internal libvirt mechanisms increases number of memory copies and
  it is just a single-threaded encryption mechanism. Because of that
  transfer between source and destination is around 2Gb/s on a 10Gb
  network. Given how fast memory is it effectively prevents live
  migrations from finishing without entering post-copy mode. Most
  operators are turning tunnelling off to increase convergence without
  using such hammers like post-copy or pausing an instance during
  live migration.
* It also has some limitations, e.g., selective disk migration does
  not work when tunnelling is enabled, which means that by default it
  is not possible to block live migrate image-backed VMs with additional
  volumes atteched
* Default value of live_migration_tunnelled - None - supposed to
  choose the best option for encrypting live migration basing on
  e.g., availability of native encryption in hypervisor. However,
  this will only solve problems with LM limitations when libvirt
  tunnelling is in use. Poor performance will still be an issue.

Change-Id: I0323e8bb2ded938522c15b220b84ddfc606e1c97
'}]
commit_message:
Change default value of live_migration_tunnelled to False

Given the impact of libvirt tunnelling mechanism this patch changes
default value of live_migration_tunnelled to False. There are few
reasons to do that:
* Internal libvirt mechanisms increases number of memory copies and
  it is just a single-threaded encryption mechanism. Because of that
  transfer between source and destination is around 2Gb/s on a 10Gb
  network. Given how fast memory is it effectively prevents live
  migrations from finishing without entering post-copy mode. Most
  operators are turning tunnelling off to increase convergence without
  using such hammers like post-copy or pausing an instance during
  live migration.
* It also has some limitations, e.g., selective disk migration does
  not work when tunnelling is enabled, which means that by default it
  is not possible to block live migrate image-backed VMs with additional
  volumes atteched
* Default value of live_migration_tunnelled - None - supposed to
  choose the best option for encrypting live migration basing on
  e.g., availability of native encryption in hypervisor. However,
  this will only solve problems with LM limitations when libvirt
  tunnelling is in use. Poor performance will still be an issue.

Change-Id: I0323e8bb2ded938522c15b220b84ddfc606e1c97

Adding summary views for Searchlight resources

This patch adds registrations that expose summary (drawer) views to
Searchlight's Horizon panel.

To test, make sure you copy over:

../searchlight-ui/searchlight_ui/enabled/_1001_project_search_panel.py

since it has changed.

Co-Authored-By: Tyr Johanson <tyr@hpe.com>

commit_message:
Add python packages for SNI support in tests

This adds python packages required for SNI support to ensure that tox

commit_message:
flavor-id should be only integer or UUID

nova flavor-create should only work with
flavorid as an integer or UUID, but
currently a flavor is created even if the
user enters a string, etc.
Included a condition to check if the user
enters anything else than an interger or
UUID.
Closes-Bug: #1426806

Change-Id: Iaa845a5e1f3e6ae04cc85f9d2f7f32435cd8a123

commit_message:
Added documentation draft jobs for nodejs-based projects

This patch adds documentation draft builds and job groups for our
javascript projects. They will upload the constructed documentation
to static.openstack.org so we can make sure it's built correctly.

The jobs depend on bindep to ensure that all necessary
dependencies have been installed, so if you're missing something,
please check bindep.txt in your project's root directory.

As we don't quite yet know whether the projects' docs builds pass,
they have been set to non-voting.

Change-Id: Ic03c731241870443e47e1565119f49cb039f6bd4
Depends-on: Ica6a641a99a642a8b77120e8b747535b819d7c0b
Depends-on: If053677bb48898cf56001e6648605b5420567417

commit_message:
Skip SNMPv1/2 (V-38660) checks in gate

The CI gate job images have SNMPv1/2 configurations applied and
they are in the process of being removed. This patch should get
the openstack-ansible-security gate jobs unblocked by skipping
V-38660 temporarily.

When https://review.openstack.org/#/c/354819/ merges and new
images are deployed, this task won't need to be skipped.

Change-Id: I2bad2ce8bb5ba73356d224ce1093bc4f19fe75b9

commit_message:
Fix H404/405 violations in novaclient/v2/[h-s]

There is a lot of H404/405 violations in novaclient, and it is better
to fix those to have a better doc string for class/methods.

This patch fixes these violations for [h-s] files under  novaclient/v2
folder.

As there are lot of violations and cannot be fixed in single patches,
So separating those in multiple patches for easy review.

Change-Id: I809692f27d8dd11a0ad550b0b6c3957e81d4059c
Partial-Bug: #1521899

commit_message:
Fix H404/405 violations in novaclient/*.py

There is a lot of H404/405 violations in novaclient, and it is better
to fix those to have a better doc string for class/methods.

This patch fixes these violations for below files-
-exceptions.py
-service_catalog.py
-shell.py
-utils.py

As there are lot of violations and cannot be fixed in single patches,
So separating those in multiple patches for easy review.

Change-Id: I73356d703b4f897fb12ae5c1719bc626c500f554
Partial-Bug: #1521899

commit_message:
Prints "id" in place of "agent_id" for nova-agent commands.

When creating a new entity, most APIs return a response which includes
"id" to represent a new id. However, only agent API returns "agent_id"
as a new entity. This patch changes "agent_id" to "id" for providing
consistency from the viewpoint of whole Nova API.

Closes-Bug: 1306381

Change-Id: I79bcea6d007f7bd4fff023d819c83a2191b22003

commit_message:
Revert "Add debug logging to revocation event checking"

This caused the keystone logs in a normal run to grow to
over 1G. This is unsustainable.

This should be reverted, and a more targeted approach added
if there is need for per request logging here. 

This reverts commit d2ee07b8e7654069ca549d2737de801c403f0f19.

Change-Id: I1d1da2b8ebd48239fbe3c2d36cbd3a0929f38786

Add columns support for share-replica-list

The share-replica-list command does not allow specifying
the required columns to format the output of the command.

Add parameter "--columns" and add a unit test for that.

commit_message:
remove compact option from xtrabackup

Using the --compact option with xtrabackup has been shown to cause
crashes when used during an SST to transfer data between nodes:

https://bugs.launchpad.net/percona-xtrabackup/+bug/1192834

Based on DBA advice, we are disabling this option.

Closes-Bug: #1590166
Change-Id: I23fd5e36b74163fe97cf983cdc4b1d5678d94e7b

commit_message:
describe a process for managing community-wide goals

One of the outcomes of the discussion at the leadership training session
earlier this year was the idea that the TC should set some
community-wide goals for accomplishing specific technical tasks to get
the projects synced up and moving in the same direction.

This patch includes the proposed process for managing those goals, a
template for describing a goal, the placeholder for goals for the Ocata
cycle, and a tool for mechanically generating part of the documents.

I had help with reviews and drafts of some portions of this text from a
bunch of other folks including jroll, dtroyer, johnthetubaguy, spamaps,
mordred, ttx, notmorgan, thingee, and amrith.

Change-Id: I46cc66eafe9dbcfda94fb6a1a8c66c2ca77de45a
Signed-off-by: Doug Hellmann <doug@doughellmann.com>

commit_message:
Add support for rolling upgrades to keystone-manage

Add all the commands to keystone-manage as well as stubs for
the logic in the migration helpers, for the expand, migrate
and contract cycles of a rolling upgrade.

Follow-on patchs will add the logic to the migration helpers.

Partially Implements blueprint manage-migration
Change-Id: I9f138fe0bcbf5ffbb98e6fcebd7d897329a301b7

Fix order of arguments in assertEqual

Some tests used incorrect order assertEqual(observed, expected).

The correct order expected by testtools is
assertEqual(expected, observed).

commit_message:
Use non-bracketed version of addresses for keystone.initialize

os-cloud-config will add brackets around IPv6 addresses [1] as
needed, we can't use bracketed version for the ssh command
so this change restores use of KeystoneAdminVip output,
previously removed by I0cf9ada1110f6b1452480039c136aee1fc3ccc82

1. https://github.com/openstack/os-cloud-config/blob/master/os_cloud_config/keystone.py#L542

Closes-Bug: 1612463

Change-Id: I7d82f93b9d4e38e6a2da5c6b6a6d7b803890b440
(cherry picked from commit 3665888fe4c045b40c5a3a98ebbf727ed2f21d9f)

commit_message:
Move Nova settings out of puppet/compute.yaml

This finishes moving most of the config settings out of
compute.yaml for Nova and into the proper nova-* services.

Only the bind port/VIP related Nova settings remain now and those
will be dealt with in a follow up patch.

commit_message:
Change pick array order to set the Keystone password in Cinder API profile

Master manual deployment fails with
Must pass keystone_password to Class[Cinder::Api] at
/etc/puppet/modules/tripleo/manifests/profile/base/cinder/api.pp

Changing the parameters order in a pick call seems to
set the parameter correctly, in this case the pick function
should not get the value if it's unde or ""

Change-Id: I1dd165bfcd8a421185538301a4e4d9b3dc372edc
Closes-Bug: 1612384

commit_message:
Disk collection period has inconsistent collection timestamps

_last_disk_collect_time should be measured in prepare_run which is
before the actual check runs. This will make sure the disk collect
time is consistent with disk_collection_period.

Change-Id: I75ef4ca75aa22172ab6203dd8fe21d2e0b7c91f9
Closes-Bug: #1613463

commit_message:
remove compact option from xtrabackup

Using the --compact option with xtrabackup has been shown to cause
crashes when used during an SST to transfer data between nodes:

https://bugs.launchpad.net/percona-xtrabackup/+bug/1192834

Based on DBA advice, we are disabling this option.

Closes-Bug: #1590166
Change-Id: I23fd5e36b74163fe97cf983cdc4b1d5678d94e7b
(cherry picked from commit 1f0cfa235acca67a953dfbff828d020da5dd734c)

copy.deepcopy(). This behavior is inconsistent.

Closes-Bug: #1613409

commit_message:
Support copy() in Sentinel

The current impl of Sentinel doesn't return the singleton
instance when used with copy.copy(), but it does with
copy.deepcopy(). This behavior is inconsistent.

This patch adds support for copy.copy() as well as a UT.

Change-Id: I33225f5a6e62be9647edacd4b3bd25702e6d8141
Closes-Bug: #1613409

commit_message:
provision: require admin user before creating nova flavor

Require to first create admin keystone before trying to create nova
flavors.
The reason of such a change is that we figured when running a single
node deployment, we need to make sure to create the flavor at the right
time in the catalog otherwise we have seen some cases where the flavor
was created before having Nova API actually working.

Change-Id: I299d4c372da702232eaa7cb34b690e372f56e701

subject: [mitaka-only] Fix up OPM symlinks before AODH migration
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-08-15 12:40:50.000000000', 'files': ['extraconfig/tasks/major_upgrade_pacemaker_migrations.sh'], 'message': "[mitaka-only] Fix up OPM symlinks before AODH migration

If upgrading Kilo -> Liberty -> Mitaka, the AODH migration fails because
the aodh puppet module is newly introduced in Liberty OPM, but it's not
symlinked from /etc/puppet/modules, as this symlinking only happens
during image building (and when starting on Kilo images, the symlink
isn't present).

Suggestion that the symlinks should be handled by OPM packaging received
pushback that such solution doesn't fit all use cases for the OPM
package.

Here we fix up the already broken Liberty deployment right before AODH
migration happens. A solution to prevent such broken state from
happening in the first place will be implemented for bug #1613211.

Change-Id: I577e6344feeda77bde08387e1b1e3aad6c380c4f
Related-Bug: #1613211
"}]
commit_message:
[mitaka-only] Fix up OPM symlinks before AODH migration

If upgrading Kilo -> Liberty -> Mitaka, the AODH migration fails because
the aodh puppet module is newly introduced in Liberty OPM, but it's not
symlinked from /etc/puppet/modules, as this symlinking only happens
during image building (and when starting on Kilo images, the symlink
isn't present).

Suggestion that the symlinks should be handled by OPM packaging received
pushback that such solution doesn't fit all use cases for the OPM
package.

Here we fix up the already broken Liberty deployment right before AODH
migration happens. A solution to prevent such broken state from
happening in the first place will be implemented for bug #1613211.

Change-Id: I577e6344feeda77bde08387e1b1e3aad6c380c4f
Related-Bug: #1613211

subject: Fix tempest neutron setup tasks
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-08-16 10:46:19.000000000', 'files': ['tasks/tempest_resources.yml'], 'message': 'Fix tempest neutron setup tasks

1) Allow the creation of network types outside the norm of vxlan/vlan.
2) tempest_public_physical_net_type was used in the resources setup
   tasks, while it was defined in defaults as
   tempest_public_net_physical_type.
3) Consolidate the public network setup task from "if flat" and "if
   vlan" into something that will accommodate other network types
   such as local.
4) Do not require a segmentation id on private network setup,
   enabling the use of types other than vxlan/vlan.

Change-Id: I54de9862686f9c67266d4c7335f00c0553202c85
'}]
commit_message:
Fix tempest neutron setup tasks

1) Allow the creation of network types outside the norm of vxlan/vlan.
2) tempest_public_physical_net_type was used in the resources setup
   tasks, while it was defined in defaults as
   tempest_public_net_physical_type.
3) Consolidate the public network setup task from "if flat" and "if
   vlan" into something that will accommodate other network types
   such as local.
4) Do not require a segmentation id on private network setup,
   enabling the use of types other than vxlan/vlan.

Change-Id: I54de9862686f9c67266d4c7335f00c0553202c85

commit_message:
Added systemd resolver files to Ubuntu16.04 and RHEL7

This change adds the systemd resolver file to the `copy_from_host`
include list. This will ensure that all of the resolver information
on a given host is also present within a container.

commit_message:
Fine tuning of stack script

Some services like zookeeper and kafka need some time to come
up before trying to start a service that depends on it.  Give
some time between services on stop/start for services to die
or come all the way up.

Change-Id: I62552ece2be0d55106a387b14d15c1691b1ac497

commit_message:
Use neutron for network name -> id resolution

The 2.36 microversion deprecates the nova proxy APIs for looking up a
network from neutron. The CLI will lookup a network by name for
booting a server as a convenience.

Over 90% of clouds now have neutron. We use a service catalog lookup
to assume that neutron is available, and if not fall back to our
proxy. This should mostly shield people from the 2.36 transition.

To test this we add support in our fake client for the neutron network
lookup. Comments were also left about some cleanups we should do in
other parts of the shell testing for net lookup.

Related to blueprint deprecate-api-proxies

Change-Id: I4f809de4f7efb913c814f132f5b3482731c588c5

commit_message:
Look up image names directly in glance

This does a lookup directly to the image service for name => id
mapping of images. This is required to move on to supporting the
2.36 microversion since that microversion makes the compute
image API proxy return a 404, so before the client can support
that microversion it has to first drop it's usage of the proxy
API.

Because of the way the FakeHTTPClient was stubbing the image
API proxy and the tests are not passing uuids for image IDs,
there is a lot of cleaning up of the tests to make this work
with a fake glance v2 API backend. The tests were basically
false though since you can't do 'nova image-show 1', but because
the stubs mask that it's just been a mountain of lies that has to
be cleaned up here.

As a side effect of fixing a bunch of the tests, this also
makes debugging assert_called less terrible with a better error
message.

Co-Authored-By: Matt Riedemann <mriedem@us.ibm.com>

Related to blueprint deprecate-api-proxies

Change-Id: Iaff3999eafb7d746e5c6032f07ce0756f7b5e868

commit_message:
Add connector for vmdk volumes

Change I743e676372703e74178c79683dd622d530981e04 removed volume
backend driver calls for creating and restoring volume backups.
The overridden methods for creating and restoring backups in
the VMDK driver is no longer called and this breaks the backup-
restore of volumes created by the VMDK driver. The Cinder backup
manager now uses initiator connectors for creating and restoring
backups for all volume backends. The patch adds a connector for
vmdk volumes to fix the backup-restore for the VMDK driver.

DocImpact

Change-Id: Ia1a20f93780593b1efbb74484c3fdd3ca3564290
Partial-bug: #1602660

commit_message:
Remove the using of dict.get() in assertIsNone

The assertIsNone(dict.get(key)) will pass in the
following two cases:
A. if there is no key in the dictionary.
B. if the related value of the key is None.

In this patch, we will replace it with
assertNotIn(key, dict) to eliminate these vague
assertion.

Change-Id: I56ff5119f84d17e73011e10660ae62b4ea4dfa3c
Partial-Bug: #1613154

commit_message:
Keep config drive in swift until server deletion

Currently if configdrive_use_swift is set, config drive will be
uploaded to swift with header:
{'X-Delete-After': timeout}

Which means config drive will be removed after "timeout" seconds.
If the server is rebuilt "timeout" seconds later, config drive
won't be available, and provisioning will fail.

This commit fixes the issue by:
1. Remove 'X-Delete-After' header from 'create_object' call
2. Generate new temp url during rebuild
3. Delete config drive when tearing down server

Change-Id: I5697b3409b60e72181a805123f6d1bb1cd8c908e
Closes-Bug: 1612476

commit_message:
Remove auth line to fallback on default(omit) behaviour

Ansible openstack_full_argument_spec defines the 'auth' param
as dict.
As the enroll task defaults the 'auth' variable to None, Ansible
first sets that to string 'None' which makes it unconvertible to
dict.
Removing the line to leverage the default(omit) fixes the issue.

Change-Id: Ib442fdca64e375eb8025212067032c93934d5d94
Closes-Bug: LP1612196

commit_message:
Don't use moment.js for parsing ISO8601 dates

Native Date constructor is reliable enough to parse ISO8601 dates
and ~10x faster than moment.js, so it's better to use it to
improve performance on large number of nodes/tasks.

Implements blueprint ui-deployment-history

Change-Id: Id5ff166a0c82e21fef418a5179bb2909ae962a8d

commit_message:
Set OS_AUTH_TOKEN to dummy string, instead of empty space

Setting the OS_AUTH_TOKEN to empty space as stated on the docs
and env-vars no longer works, it errors out a message from requests

revisions:
[{'number': 6, 'created': '2016-08-12 04:55:32.000000000', 'files': ['murano/dsl/murano_object.py', 'murano/dsl/object_store.py'], 'message': "Don't put non-initialized objects into ObjectStore

Because object model deserialization happens in
several phases nested objects without fixed ID
will be created again upon each pass and only
the last one will be the property value. Previously
created objects remain in the ObjectStore but were
not initialized. This is going to cause issues once garbage
collection is implemented because it may attempt to
collect uninitialized objects.

With this commit objects that are not fully initialized are
not copied into the permanent object store anymore.

Change-Id: I6924b93d79c69181fe2cc8baa329a3822892af3c
"}]
commit_message:
Don't put non-initialized objects into ObjectStore

Because object model deserialization happens in
several phases nested objects without fixed ID
will be created again upon each pass and only
the last one will be the property value. Previously
created objects remain in the ObjectStore but were
not initialized. This is going to cause issues once garbage
collection is implemented because it may attempt to
collect uninitialized objects.

With this commit objects that are not fully initialized are
not copied into the permanent object store anymore.

Change-Id: I6924b93d79c69181fe2cc8baa329a3822892af3c

commit_message:
Fix small bugs in pagination

Fix bugs in file sahara/db/sqlalchemy/api.py

1. In 80 line of this file there was invalid condition.
If position + limit will be equal len(objects), there
will be IndexError exception.
2. In 86 line of this file there was invalid indexing of
next marker.
3.In line 945 converting limit to int was missed.
4.In line 946 fix missprint in list limitation.
5. In line 948 was added call job_execution_get,
because get_prev_and_next_objects take marker object (not
object id string).

Change-Id: Ie52cded54db139bd89f7bd8286b5e16bb2539c44
bp: pagination

commit_message:
Fix devmode command in README

If you copy/paste the command it fails because the default location
of the quickstart artifacts are in ~/.quickstart.  This patch adds
the ".quickstart" to the beginning of the path to make it less likely
a new user will encounter an error on first run.

Change-Id: If9053fbfad4e8ccf46b0145e701b4e8b844cb41c

commit_message:
Include ServerAlias in dashboard vhost if set

There are use cases where having ServerAlias in the vhost is preferred. This
includes that option but excludes by default. It's set using an array so you can
set multiple server aliases.

I also added the virtualhost port configurator test for dashboard-http-bind on
port 80 to ensure it works on both ports.

Change-Id: I621cb2a519e92d04d60fd75e727b59250bd72e30

commit_message:
Removed Unnecessary cache updation for the router ports

OVS plugin unnecessary tries to poll Neutron server for Router list
even no matching ports are found as per the included devices regular expression.
File ovs_ports.json is constantly updated every collection interval, which should
not happen when there are no matching ports. It affects the scale environment where
larger number of router ports are added .

Change-Id: If3ef1a50b118fe08629332180fa863f4bf862ef0
Closes-Bug: 1610823
Co-Authored-By: Alok Kumar Maurya <alok-kumar.maurya@hpe.com>
Co-Authored-By: Ashish Kumar Gupta <ashish-kumar.gupta@hpe.com>

commit_message:
Don't use moment.js for parsing ISO8601 dates

Native Date constructor is reliable enough to parse ISO8601 dates
and ~10x faster than moment.js, so it's better to use it to
improve performance on large number of nodes/tasks.

Implements blueprint ui-deployment-history

Change-Id: Id5ff166a0c82e21fef418a5179bb2909ae962a8d

subject: Add a reminder to remove Route.interface field
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2016-08-16 13:38:03.000000000', 'files': ['os_vif/objects/route.py'], 'message': 'Add a reminder to remove Route.interface field

Nova never sets the Route.interface value to anything but
None which fails with an error:

"ValueError: Fieldinterface' cannot be None"

This looks like a carry-over from the nova.network.model.Route
class which has an interface field which is set to None by default
but that field is never set to anything else in Nova, neither
for nova-network or Neutron.

Furthermore, it looks like 'interface' is not something that's
in the Route data model in Neutron either.

We don't hit this in the gate because the subnets we're testing
with don't have host_routes set.

The ValueError was fixed in Nova by not setting the attribute:

1d57c1fd53e930b02c3ce0e9914f95ef68dd1f87

This change adds a TODO to remove it in version 2.0 of the Route object.

Change-Id: Ib25a79514fe4335f4df222c02fefc9da62fe04ce
Closes-Bug: #1612812
'}]
commit_message:
Add a reminder to remove Route.interface field

Nova never sets the Route.interface value to anything but
None which fails with an error:

"ValueError: Fieldinterface' cannot be None"

This looks like a carry-over from the nova.network.model.Route
class which has an interface field which is set to None by default
but that field is never set to anything else in Nova, neither
for nova-network or Neutron.

Furthermore, it looks like 'interface' is not something that's
in the Route data model in Neutron either.

We don't hit this in the gate because the subnets we're testing
with don't have host_routes set.

The ValueError was fixed in Nova by not setting the attribute:

1d57c1fd53e930b02c3ce0e9914f95ef68dd1f87

This change adds a TODO to remove it in version 2.0 of the Route object.

Change-Id: Ib25a79514fe4335f4df222c02fefc9da62fe04ce
Closes-Bug: #1612812

commit_message:
Skip checking samples in coverage job

TaskSampleTestCase is not quick stuff. Tests from this testcase tests
yaml/json files which are not relate to tests coverage of Rally code.
Also, coverage job launchs this slow testcase twice.
Let's use environment variable to identify job name and skip whole test
case in case of coverage job.

PS: coverage is not change in comparison with previous commit, where
    TaskSampleTestCase is launched. It is one more proof that this testcase
    doesn't have any unique calls to rally code.

Change-Id: If0925bc37198092f5d9efadb6591ced25d75212c

subject: Handle race condition of sync from multiple decision engines
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-07-08 00:08:04.000000000', 'files': ['watcher/decision_engine/sync.py', 'watcher/decision_engine/goal/efficacy/indicators.py', 'watcher/db/sqlalchemy/models.py', 'watcher/tests/api/v1/test_strategies.py', 'watcher/common/exception.py', 'watcher/db/sqlalchemy/api.py'], 'message': 'Handle race condition of sync from multiple decision engines

To avoid race condition of goal/strategy creation when sync from
multiple decision engines, takes the following changes:

* makes name column in goal/strategy table as unique, so that creating
  a new goal/strategy with same name as existed one would cause
  AlreadyExists exception.
* refactors goal/strategy creation code to be aware of another engine
  possibly doing the same thing.
* comparison of goal with efficacy specification is changed to check
  source code of schema instead of schema object, or else a goal
  created by one engine will be treated stale and deleted immediately.

Change-Id: Id65225cdbacb77f53ba7330186f820a721337356
Closes-Bug: #1598946
'}]
commit_message:
Handle race condition of sync from multiple decision engines

To avoid race condition of goal/strategy creation when sync from
multiple decision engines, takes the following changes:

* makes name column in goal/strategy table as unique, so that creating
  a new goal/strategy with same name as existed one would cause
  AlreadyExists exception.
* refactors goal/strategy creation code to be aware of another engine
  possibly doing the same thing.
* comparison of goal with efficacy specification is changed to check
  source code of schema instead of schema object, or else a goal
  created by one engine will be treated stale and deleted immediately.

Change-Id: Id65225cdbacb77f53ba7330186f820a721337356
Closes-Bug: #1598946

commit_message:
add support to process measures on GET

depending on the backlog, the returned measures from get-measures
may not include what sits in carbonara backlog. to allow for more
flexibility on metricd deployments, this patch offers the ability
to allow users to get all measures even if they don't have enough
metricd workers, at the expense of responsiveness.

refresh blocks until it can process measures

Change-Id: I588ae6879474d780e8ec9e893d4ecc2b367b832e
Closes-Bug: #1603495

commit_message:
Improve node selection for partially deploy

We have a hardcoded values for a selected nodes.
Sometimes this could lead test fail when we try to
deploy both computes instead of a controller and
compute.
This fix adds a smart nodes selection by nodes
and their roles

Change-Id: Icde591cd47afb6a3e5574aea9267ef3543b7c158
Closes-Bug:1607809
(cherry picked from commit 2449f17eee608e73de71b96c79c3de0cae446397)

commit_message:
Make a FernetUtils class

By converting our module-level fernet utilities to a class, we can
extend it or modify it in ways to make the utilities work for outside
the fernet token provider. This change is in preparation to use fernet
to encrypt credentials at rest.

bp credential-encryption

Change-Id: Ia4e9fd2b8597993f006d9fea82b782085f2cdbc2

commit_message:
Change EFI fs label

If EFI partition does not have specific label
different from ISO label, then udev first creates
/dev/disk/by-label for 9660 file system and then
overrides this link with the link pointing to
EFI partition.

Change-Id: Id841c5b306940fd157aee527ad69b0995bcf9cd8
Closes-Bug: #1605740

first step is to limit their usage to download routes only.

commit_message:
Fix parameters of assertEqual are misplaced

Many assertEqual sentences don't follow assertEqual(expected, actual),
These misplaces have 2 impacts:
1, giving confusing messages when some tests failed.
2, mislead other developers, new test modules may follow these wrong pattern.

This patch fix all of them.

Change-Id: I33b5b59fda524d88386072d2058c4770a948db6f
Closes-Bug: #1604213

commit_message:
Refactoring config options of l3 agent keepalived

Refactoring configuration options for agent/l3/keepalived_state_change
to be in neutron/conf/agent/l3. This would allow centralization of all
configuration options under neutron/conf and provide an easy way to
import.

Change-Id: I18e5f683690cffd6e0ad5e35f459b86c5b3332ac
Partial-Bug: #1563069

subject: Tempest: increase ironic sync timeout
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2016-08-11 12:48:31.000000000', 'files': ['ironic_inspector/test/inspector_tempest_plugin/config.py'], 'message': 'Tempest: increase ironic sync timeout

Increase ironic_sync_timeout to 80 sec. Ironic default status check period
is 60 sec. But calling Ironic API to get node status takes some time, and
races appear, as result tempest job periodically fails. 80 sec would
be more than enough to make one more check.

Change-Id: I5fe0198b2ce2f1f0078c1d14aa1c367a71178097
'}]
commit_message:
Tempest: increase ironic sync timeout

Increase ironic_sync_timeout to 80 sec. Ironic default status check period
is 60 sec. But calling Ironic API to get node status takes some time, and
races appear, as result tempest job periodically fails. 80 sec would
be more than enough to make one more check.

Change-Id: I5fe0198b2ce2f1f0078c1d14aa1c367a71178097

commit_message:
Improve node selection for partially deploy

We have a hardcoded values for a selected nodes.
Sometimes this could lead test fail when we try to
deploy both computes instead of a controller and
compute.
This fix adds a smart nodes selection by nodes
and their roles

Change-Id: Icde591cd47afb6a3e5574aea9267ef3543b7c158
Closes-Bug:1607809

commit_message:
Support checkpoint metadata

Adds a spec for supporting checkpint metadata.

Currently when creating a checkpoint. The only place to add custom
information apart from the name is in the description field. This means
that tools that create checkpoints needs to use this user visible space
for their own metadata.

blueprint smaug-checkpoint-metadata

Change-Id: I0c9a5541a419932a1506481fccc5c62baf0c48f0

[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-08-11 05:36:12.000000000', 'files': ['magnum/tests/unit/db/base.py'], 'message': 'Use memory mode for sqlite in db test

Config option sqlite_db is deprecated in
0a1bae9859079fb21a03716be947c5f1da6db0a2, and deprecate argument
sqlite_db in method set_defaults in
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/350945/, should use config option

commit_message:
Use memory mode for sqlite in db test

Config option sqlite_db is deprecated in
0a1bae9859079fb21a03716be947c5f1da6db0a2, and deprecate argument
sqlite_db in method set_defaults in
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/350945/, should use config option
connection instead. For magnum, we test database with sqlite in
memory mode [1] as below:

CONF.set_default('connection', "sqlite://", group='database')

and don't use config option sqlite_db, so remove unused code.

[1]http://docs.sqlalchemy.org/en/rel_1_0/core/engines.html#sqlite

Change-Id: I69f7d7c1f84b577db1fc2de0e1106b61d1cceac6

commit_message:
HAHT - persist pushed data

Use optional config parameter persist_data=true (case insensitive)
to enable persisting data. eg.
$ openstack congress datasource create push push
        --config persist_data=True

Closes-Bug: 1600015
Partially implements blueprint: high-availability-design

Change-Id: I2dd4fb1c4baf61281bd26ec64d7f02fedae18ac1

Ironic doesn't provide prebuilt images for the old deprecated deploy

commit_message:
Ensure we alway build old Ironic ramdisk

Ironic doesn't provide prebuilt images for the old deprecated deploy
ramdisk this must always be built by devstack or manually provided. In
the job we don't manually provide the ramdisk and after the recent
refactor building the ramdisk is explictly disabled by the job this
means devstack fails, because it doesn't have a ramdisk to use. This
patch reenables building the ramdisk for the job that uses the old
ramdisk.

Change-Id: I0f4d90d90dc47f102a52cba242ba9533a11cb1a2

The console functional tests were written under the assumption
of how the gate jobs work in our CI system, but with a local
devstack you might have a different configuration. For example,
we don't run the nova-novnc service in the gate but it's enabled
by default in devstack, so functional console tests for vnc will
fail in a local default devstack setup.

This change fixes the console functional tests to handle the case
that a valid response is returned and adds a check for how the

commit_message:
Handle successful response in console functional tests

The console functional tests were written under the assumption
of how the gate jobs work in our CI system, but with a local
devstack you might have a different configuration. For example,
we don't run the nova-novnc service in the gate but it's enabled
by default in devstack, so functional console tests for vnc will
fail in a local default devstack setup.

This change fixes the console functional tests to handle the case
that a valid response is returned and adds a check for how the
response looks so we're at least validating something.

Change-Id: I3505c9955d032301b34764f67466c467a79ed9fb
Closes-Bug: #1613435

commit_message:
Use assertEqual() instead of assertDictEqual()

In unittest2, assertDictEqual() is implemented by
using != operator to compare two dicts. So is
assertEqual() in testtools. assertEqual() in testtools
is able to handle dict, list, set and so on. So we
just call assertEqual() to make the unit tests simpler.

Change-Id: Id40c618206a78ae340e7cb6cf77f895371434f8e

commit_message:
Avoid duplicate sections in generator output

Because option groups can be specified as either bare strings or
OptGroup objects, it is possible to end up with duplicate sections
in the resulting output file.  This is confusing, and can cause
problems for config management systems so we should avoid doing it.

This change avoids the dupes by always keying the group list on
the group name, but including the OptGroup object in the data
when available so the output code can make use of the extra
information in an OptGroup.

Co-Authored-By: Alexis Lee <lxsli@hpe.com>
Change-Id: I2cd8ae87a1f573b5837d292abcf7babf5d88bee5
Closes-Bug: 1568820

commit_message:
Fix interface configuration for tempest gate

The tempest gate is failing due to tempest being unable to boot
instances. This is due to the veth peer not being setup correctly, and
the linuxbridge configuration being incorrect

This PR fixes the veth peer and and the neutron configuration
options.

Change-Id: Iaffb5f95ab59918feb5e498bbdc6a6325abaa4d4

subject: Enable DeprecationWarning in test environments
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-08-09 22:50:37.000000000', 'files': ['tox.ini'], 'message': 'Enable DeprecationWarning in test environments

Many deprecations are triggered early (on imports, for example)
before the warnings are enabled by the WarningsFixture in the
base test class.

To make sure all DeprecationWarning messages are emitted we enable
them via the PYTHONWARNINGS environment variable.

Change-Id: I417155f34fa4054df2c73506143af876ecd727a2
'}]
commit_message:
Enable DeprecationWarning in test environments

Many deprecations are triggered early (on imports, for example)
before the warnings are enabled by the WarningsFixture in the
base test class.

To make sure all DeprecationWarning messages are emitted we enable
them via the PYTHONWARNINGS environment variable.

Change-Id: I417155f34fa4054df2c73506143af876ecd727a2

commit_message:
loadimpact perf improvement with batch vsctl/native commands

WIP
***
Few modifications to group some ovs-vsctl ops as transactions.
Some of the vsctl calls cannot be combined due to their
inter-dependencies for data/logic as it is structured in the
current agent code. Also there is open flow add/mod calls
to ofctl which also could be optimized if they can be combined.
Bundling ofctl flows need OpenFlow v1.4, and is not done.

This patch is to get some early feedback to judge if it is
headed in the right direction, and whether it will bring in
some perf improvements in 100+ (many) node environments.
Please help in testing the patch in your many node env.
If the results are positive, I'll continue working on
this to further optimize.

The changes in this patch applies equally to vsctl- and
native- ovsdb plugins.

Change-Id: Id025538628de775cb3010587040f04312b1d01b2
Closes-Bug: 1264608

revisions:
[{'number': 7, 'created': '2016-03-14 06:26:12.000000000', 'files': ['neutron/plugins/common/utils.py', 'neutron/plugins/ml2/drivers/type_tunnel.py', 'neutron/tests/unit/common/test_utils.py'], 'message': "Huge mem usage during tunnel type driver initialization

Currently if large ranges are specified in ml2_conf.ini for
tunnel ID ranges like 'vni_ranges = 1001:16777215', the neutron
service will fail to start. This happens for gre type as well.
On a node with memory pressure the service may bail out with
MemoryError. This is due to high memory use associated with
the use of 'set' python primitive. In the TunnelTypeDriver's
initialization, during sync_allocations() 'set' is used to
build a unique range of tunnel IDs, the list of IDs to remove
and missing list for allocation. When large ranges are
specified this leads to very high memory use as the entire
sequential range is built out in memory to form union,
difference etc. This patch addresses this by operating on
ranges directly as they are received from configuration.
Without building out the entire set/list of sequential numbers,
it de-duplicates the ranges in the list and builds the list to
remove and allocate. This change brings down the memory usage
in the order of GBs and finishes initialization within the
same time, or even better.

As mentioned in the bug there are many other scaling issues to
consider before neutron can handle such large ranges. These
issues are not addressed in this patch. This patch only reduces
the memory use during type driver initialization. With this
patch the vmem usage of neutron-server is within 600-700MB range,
whereas with the 'set' it was climbing to > 1.5-2GB. With this
change q-svc service takes 25-30 mins to start completely on a
4GB VM running devstack, when a range of 1:16777215 is specified.

Change-Id: Ie0702c0363492ba8fbc240688635a53857c835fd
Closes-Bug: 1426904
Related-Bug: 1326634
"}]
commit_message:
Huge mem usage during tunnel type driver initialization

Currently if large ranges are specified in ml2_conf.ini for
tunnel ID ranges like 'vni_ranges = 1001:16777215', the neutron
service will fail to start. This happens for gre type as well.
On a node with memory pressure the service may bail out with
MemoryError. This is due to high memory use associated with
the use of 'set' python primitive. In the TunnelTypeDriver's
initialization, during sync_allocations() 'set' is used to
build a unique range of tunnel IDs, the list of IDs to remove
and missing list for allocation. When large ranges are
specified this leads to very high memory use as the entire
sequential range is built out in memory to form union,
difference etc. This patch addresses this by operating on
ranges directly as they are received from configuration.
Without building out the entire set/list of sequential numbers,
it de-duplicates the ranges in the list and builds the list to
remove and allocate. This change brings down the memory usage
in the order of GBs and finishes initialization within the
same time, or even better.

As mentioned in the bug there are many other scaling issues to
consider before neutron can handle such large ranges. These
issues are not addressed in this patch. This patch only reduces
the memory use during type driver initialization. With this
patch the vmem usage of neutron-server is within 600-700MB range,
whereas with the 'set' it was climbing to > 1.5-2GB. With this
change q-svc service takes 25-30 mins to start completely on a
4GB VM running devstack, when a range of 1:16777215 is specified.

Change-Id: Ie0702c0363492ba8fbc240688635a53857c835fd
Closes-Bug: 1426904
Related-Bug: 1326634

commit_message:
Fix Scheduled Operation Creation failed

If the parameter called "description" is passed by "None" value,
the scheduled operation creation will be failed with value error.
It needs to set the value validation about the scheduled operation object.

Closes-Bug: #1613531

commit_message:
Allow to skip kernel cleanup

For some use cases, it can be useful to keep all the kernels
and not just keep the latest one. Add a parameter that allows
it, and continue cleaning up kernels by default.

Change-Id: Ia6e6c1fa18e3724c1eb89226151d81e9e748b793

commit_message:
Fix Trigger Creation Failed

When we create a trigger, it throws a exception like
"Unable to create trigger". The reason is that python-smaugclient
has changed the return value of trigger creation.
So it needs to update dashboard as well.

Change-Id: I683cc699adc89a5cee7da21d081d6d761b22370f
Closes-Bug: #1613587

revisions:
[{'number': 4, 'created': '2016-08-15 16:55:40.000000000', 'files': ['templates/cluster.cnf.j2', 'releasenotes/notes/xtrabackup-compact-disable-8ae9215207147ebc.yaml'], 'message': 'remove compact option from xtrabackup

Using the --compact option with xtrabackup has been shown to cause
crashes when used during an SST to transfer data between nodes:

https://bugs.launchpad.net/percona-xtrabackup/+bug/1192834

Based on DBA advice, we are disabling this option.

Closes-Bug: #1590166
Change-Id: I23fd5e36b74163fe97cf983cdc4b1d5678d94e7b
'}]
commit_message:
remove compact option from xtrabackup

Using the --compact option with xtrabackup has been shown to cause
crashes when used during an SST to transfer data between nodes:

https://bugs.launchpad.net/percona-xtrabackup/+bug/1192834

Based on DBA advice, we are disabling this option.

Closes-Bug: #1590166
Change-Id: I23fd5e36b74163fe97cf983cdc4b1d5678d94e7b

The code in [1] accidentally left api-report generation on
during pep8 (via tox.ini). We probably don't want to gen the
API report with every pep8; although ATM its pretty fast.

commit_message:
Don't run api-report during pep8

The code in [1] accidentally left api-report generation on
during pep8 (via tox.ini). We probably don't want to gen the
API report with every pep8; although ATM its pretty fast.

This patch removes the api report generation from pep8.
It can be run using: tox -e api-report

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/338571/

Change-Id: I8f7eeb0e9dffcf93c89f2dd5a8ec0befb8f77abe

commit_message:
Fix allowance of Deploy environment action

Previously action's allow() method didn't consider situation when
component was deleted from deployed environment as the valid case
to show the button. This patch fixes that by simply checking
env's status to be 'pending' or 'deploy failure'.

Change-Id: I40d62d4fcb620e7f2ffc515884c755abf6b8421c
Closes-bug: #1594354

Do not show fuelmenu while applying 9.x

The updater script is still on development so we have to use
bootstrap_admin_node.sh. Also there is an issue in devops that
is preventing fuelmenu appearing. Lasts, we are not able to
quit from fuelmenu after it appears.

Related-bug:1607402

The updater script is still on development so we have to use
bootstrap_admin_node.sh. Also there is an issue in devops that
is preventing fuelmenu appearing. Lasts, we are not able to
quit from fuelmenu after it appears.

Related-bug:1607402

subject: Enable DeprecationWarning in test environments
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-08-09 22:36:59.000000000', 'files': ['tox.ini'], 'message': 'Enable DeprecationWarning in test environments

Many deprecations are triggered early (on imports, for example)
before the warnings are enabled by the WarningsFixture in the
base test class.

To make sure all DeprecationWarning messages are emitted we enable
them via the PYTHONWARNINGS environment variable.

Change-Id: Ibdc550407996a7765b8ff2f82c07822a06cd3d03
'}]
commit_message:
Enable DeprecationWarning in test environments

Many deprecations are triggered early (on imports, for example)
before the warnings are enabled by the WarningsFixture in the
base test class.

To make sure all DeprecationWarning messages are emitted we enable
them via the PYTHONWARNINGS environment variable.

Change-Id: Ibdc550407996a7765b8ff2f82c07822a06cd3d03

commit_message:
Ignore case when comparing wwns in Pure FC driver

We would previously just assume the wwpns in our connector were lower-case
and this was not valid for all systems. We will now compare with all
lower case strings.

Change-Id: Icdb818c97fc7810b5276b83debf8e75fe48fd15d
Closes-Bug: #1612866

  which caused the whole wf_ex.task_executions collection with
  a DB query to find a single object

  'task_executions' of workflow execution object  where possible

commit_message:
Put, post operations implemented for environments

Implementation of environment operations moved to library package.
Code for searching objects by ids and names extracted to the library
function.
Exceptions propagation added to example config. It is useful for
testing and troubleshooting to have error message not only in logs
but in the API response too.
Tuningbox errors hierarchy added to the project.

subject: Enable DeprecationWarning in test environments
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-08-09 23:43:11.000000000', 'files': ['tox.ini'], 'message': 'Enable DeprecationWarning in test environments

Many deprecations are triggered early (on imports, for example)
before the warnings are enabled by the WarningsFixture in the
base test class.

To make sure all DeprecationWarning messages are emitted we enable
them via the PYTHONWARNINGS environment variable.

Change-Id: Iaf16677b18e40c9054b7053b30979603ea205bbb
'}]
commit_message:
Enable DeprecationWarning in test environments

Many deprecations are triggered early (on imports, for example)
before the warnings are enabled by the WarningsFixture in the
base test class.

To make sure all DeprecationWarning messages are emitted we enable
them via the PYTHONWARNINGS environment variable.

Change-Id: Iaf16677b18e40c9054b7053b30979603ea205bbb

commit_message:
Move other-requirements.txt to bindep.txt

The default filename for documenting binary dependencies has been
changed from "other-requirements.txt" to "bindep.txt" with the release
of bindep 2.1.0. While the previous name is still supported, it will
be deprecated.

Move the file around to follow this change.

Note that this change is self-testing, the OpenStack CI infrastructure
will use a "bindep.txt" file to setup nodes for testing.

For more information about bindep, see also:
http://docs.openstack.org/infra/manual/drivers.html#package-requirements
http://docs.openstack.org/infra/bindep/

As well as this announcement:
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2016-August/101590.html

Change-Id: I8cfb09ff8ab41f672e2fa129b0fd6c32b94a22d6
Closes-Bug: #1508502

commit_message:
monkey patch get_member(s) to get status

The only way to get the statuses for the pool member is to query
midonet API.  In order to do so, LBaaS DB mixin's get_member and
get_members are monkey patched so that member statuses are retrieved
before the response gets sent back to the user.

Change-Id: I8cfb09ff8ab41f672e2fa129b0fd6c32b94a22d6
Closes-Bug: #1508502

commit_message:
Disallow enbling a plugin with legacy tasks

When plugin contains legacy tasks enabling it makes no effect unless
propagate_task_deploy attribute is set. The plugin silently does
nothing. In order to avoid confusion enabling is prohibited explicitly.

Change-Id: I4acfb24de02ac4a5cfb25e9c8d5a3a03d5b58e77
Partial-Bug: 1596928
(cherry picked from commit 4a333ec2da82da268b493eb8bf5f4e595c86f699)

commit_message:
Rollback bay on update failure

There is a rollback mechanism in heat after the stack
update failed. There should be a rollback mechanism in
magnum after bay update failed.

This patch add new microversion 1.3 to add rollback
support for Magnum bay, user can enable rollback on bay
update failure by specifying microversion 1.3 in header(
{'OpenStack-API-Version': 'container-infra 1.3'}) and
passing 'rollback=True'(http://XXX/v1/bays/XXX/?rollback=True)
when issuing bay update reqeust.

Change-Id: Idd02769f98078702404a11dc9f7a3339ce4e22eb
Partially-Implements: blueprint bay-rollback-on-update-failure

* When inserting multiple task executions we sometimes got into
  a dead lock where transaction A would wait for an exclusive

  for a gap lock for primary key holding by transaction A.

  task executions where in case of 'join' tasks (and any tasks

commit_message:
Fix the deadlock occuring on task executions

* When inserting multiple task executions we sometimes got into
  a dead lock where transaction A would wait for an exclusive
  (write) lock on 'unique_key' of some task execution and
  transaction B would hold that lock on 'unique_key' but waiting
  for a gap lock for primary key holding by transaction A.
  Solution: remove 'unique_key' column and expand 'id for
  task executions where in case of 'join' tasks (and any tasks
  with preconditions) we just store a unique key identifying
  a certaint join task in a certain workflow. By doing that
  we eliminate two locks that transactions can possibly compete
  for and leave just one (primary key).

TODO:
* DB migration for DB schema changes

Change-Id: I8976b662504afd5cef3a331e1b44047ed3203577

reviewers: [{'_account_id': 3, 'name': 'Jenkins', 'username': 'jenkins'}, {'_account_id': 5558, 'name': 'Winson Chan', 'email': 'wcchan@stackstorm.com', 'username': 'winson-c-chan'}, {'_account_id': 6732, 'name': 'Lingxian Kong', 'email': 'anlin.kong@gmail.com', 'username': 'kong'}, {'_account_id': 7700, 'name': 'Nikolay Mahotkin', 'email': 'nikolay.makhotkin@gmail.com', 'username': 'nmakhotkin'}, {'_account_id': 8592, 'name': 'Anastasia Kuznetsova', 'email': 'akuznetsova@mirantis.com', 'username': 'nastya-kuz'}, {'_account_id': 8731, 'name': 'Renat Akhmerov', 'email': 'renat.akhmerov@gmail.com', 'username': 'rakhmerov'}, {'_account_id': 9029, 'name': 'Moshe Elisha', 'email': 'moshe.elisha@nokia.com', 'username': 'MosheElisha'}, {'_account_id': 9408, 'name': 'Michal Gershenzon', 'email': 'michal.gershenzon@gmail.com', 'username': 'Mgershen'}, {'_account_id': 18238, 'name': 'Hardik Parekh', 'email': 'hardik.parekh047@gmail.com', 'username': 'hparekh'}, {'_account_id': 19206, 'name': 'Dawid Deja', 'email': 'dawdej@gmail.com', 'username': 'ddeja'}]
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2016-08-14 05:37:21.000000000', 'files': ['mistral/services/scheduler.py', 'mistral/engine/task_handler.py', 'mistral/tests/unit/services/test_scheduler.py', 'mistral/engine/workflow_handler.py', 'mistral/tests/unit/db/v2/test_insert_or_ignore.py', 'mistral/db/sqlalchemy/model_base.py', 'mistral/db/v2/sqlalchemy/api.py', 'mistral/db/v2/sqlalchemy/models.py'], 'message': "Optimize Scheduler DB schema

* Dropped a composite index for ('execution_time', 'processing'),
  left only 'execution_time' because 'processing' is boolean
  and indexing booleans doesn't give any performance improvement
* On a high load MySQL sometimes goes into a deadlock when
  we were using unique key constraint for (unique_key, processing)
  on 'insert' and 'update' operations. It was possible to reproduce
  this kind of deadlock locally in 3 MySQL consoles where one TX
  was doing 'update ... where' and two others were doing 'insert'.
  This composite unique key constraint was dropped and replaced
  with composite primary key ('key', 'processing'). In this case
  the deadlock never happens (seems like PK are handled more
  efficiently).

TODO:
* There's still an issue with duplicate entries for delayed calls
  on operations 'update ... where' when running more than one
  scheduler. It's solvable by either using a buck update
  operation or slightly smarter handling of such error. On
  Postgres some special handling is required because it always
  switch a TX into 'rollback-only' mode on any SQL error.

Change-Id: I1f48e4b01e94c5328ccae3067e5bdd2c52d98417
"}]
commit_message:
Optimize Scheduler DB schema

* Dropped a composite index for ('execution_time', 'processing'),
  left only 'execution_time' because 'processing' is boolean
  and indexing booleans doesn't give any performance improvement
* On a high load MySQL sometimes goes into a deadlock when
  we were using unique key constraint for (unique_key, processing)
  on 'insert' and 'update' operations. It was possible to reproduce
  this kind of deadlock locally in 3 MySQL consoles where one TX
  was doing 'update ... where' and two others were doing 'insert'.
  This composite unique key constraint was dropped and replaced
  with composite primary key ('key', 'processing'). In this case
  the deadlock never happens (seems like PK are handled more
  efficiently).

TODO:
* There's still an issue with duplicate entries for delayed calls
  on operations 'update ... where' when running more than one
  scheduler. It's solvable by either using a buck update
  operation or slightly smarter handling of such error. On
  Postgres some special handling is required because it always
  switch a TX into 'rollback-only' mode on any SQL error.

Change-Id: I1f48e4b01e94c5328ccae3067e5bdd2c52d98417

commit_message:
Put py34 first in the env order of tox

When we running the tox, we are may always meeting the problem of
"db type could not be determined" on py34, we have to run the py34 first,
and then, run py27. So the patch puts py34 first on the tox.ini, which will
solve the problem above effectively.

Change-Id: I08fa26e8a637ee9ec6de9aeee932080f5194a78c
Closes-bug: #1612045

commit_message:
Further F24 kernel update

As described, I missed that we only keep *one* kernel during dib
build, so as soon as the upstream package updates, it suddenly becomes
the latest kernel and kicks our custom version out.

Guess what happened in the hours between me committing
I0769f005da1931658a5fb9e627983ed30c11d212 and the next dib build.

This will install the current latest kernel with the required patch.
As described in the comment, I have the fix committed upstream so we
can remove this whole thing when fedora rebuilds for the next stable
release (even if the patch isn't in the official stable tree yet).

Change-Id: Iafe6d88e3ac7a2ea23553a5011df920a2ee3317d

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-08-12 18:06:47.000000000', 'files': ['puppet/controller.yaml', 'overcloud.yaml', 'puppet/compute.yaml'], 'message': 'Add parameter for enabling purging configuration files

This patch adds a parameter, EnableConfigPurge, to the base nova and
neutron service files. The value is passed to their respective puppet

from the config files. The default value is set to true.

Note: this is a "semantic" backport. Instead of "service files" the

Conflicts (files do not exist in Mitaka):
	puppet/services/neutron-base.yaml
	puppet/services/nova-base.yaml

Change-Id: I32732dc2ed7a7b3187e8727592cb4add0c6b9cf6
Closes-Bug:  #1611800
(cherry picked from commit f7f514cf67274b40f0f079d5349d7e9fda9d1790)

commit_message:
Add parameter for enabling purging configuration files

This patch adds a parameter, EnableConfigPurge, to the base nova and
neutron service files. The value is passed to their respective puppet
modules to control whether resources not managed by puppet are purged
from the config files. The default value is set to true.

Note: this is a "semantic" backport. Instead of "service files" the
modified files in Mitaka are the overcloud, controller and compute
templates. As alluded to in the original commit message *only* the
::neutron and ::nova classes are affected. Follow up patches are
required to proliferate purging to other TripleO generated
configuration.

Conflicts (files do not exist in Mitaka):
	puppet/services/neutron-base.yaml
	puppet/services/nova-base.yaml

Change-Id: I32732dc2ed7a7b3187e8727592cb4add0c6b9cf6
Closes-Bug:  #1611800
(cherry picked from commit f7f514cf67274b40f0f079d5349d7e9fda9d1790)

revisions:
[{'number': 7, 'created': '2016-08-12 19:13:46.000000000', 'files': ['tempest/cmd/init.py', 'tempest/tests/cmd/test_tempest_init.py'], 'message': 'Add missing config file read to tempest init

The update_local_conf() portion of tempest init was never reading the
config file. In the case we prepopulate a tempest.conf from the global
state /etc dir this would result in tempest init duplicating options
and sections that already existed. This commit fixes the issue by
simply reading the file before we do any operations.

Also add test coverage to ensure existing settings are not overwritten.

Co-authored-by: Augustina Ragwitz <auggy@cpan.org>
Change-Id: Ie629df246fc40777f2017b78e4073ae833b64deb
'}]
commit_message:
Add missing config file read to tempest init

The update_local_conf() portion of tempest init was never reading the
config file. In the case we prepopulate a tempest.conf from the global
state /etc dir this would result in tempest init duplicating options
and sections that already existed. This commit fixes the issue by
simply reading the file before we do any operations.

Also add test coverage to ensure existing settings are not overwritten.

Co-authored-by: Augustina Ragwitz <auggy@cpan.org>
Change-Id: Ie629df246fc40777f2017b78e4073ae833b64deb

commit_message:
Add 'deployed_before' flag to cluster that forbids stop deployment

When cluster is successfuly deployed, that is, has 'operational' status,
'deployed_before' key is added to generated attributes of the cluster.
This flag then is used to determine whether stop action is allowed for
the cluster.

commit_message:
Make use of oslo-config-generator

oslo_config provide a utility for generating sample config files,
which provide more detail about opts, like Minimum/Maximum value
and Allowed values.

After this patch, new config options of masakari code should register
with masakari/conf/opts.py.

Change-Id: I8f2f7e87268498ebee7ca164db1c98ef43c279b0

Get 500 Internal server error when retrieving secret with no payload

When you store a secret without payload, and then try to retrieve
that secret's payload, you will get an error of "500 internal
server error", this patch fix that.

Closes-Bug: #1590972

commit_message:
'As of' in documentation is incorrect

The documentation has 'As of the Newton release...'. 'As of' is
used to indicate the time or date from which something starts.
In this context, that is incorrect; we want to indicate that
the Newton release is the last/end release.

Change-Id: I080694d2f4e2b6d3b53e1b2f15b96f59b3eb16cf

subject: Add nova scheduler_host_subset_size option to docs
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-08-15 12:37:17.000000000', 'files': ['doc/source/deploy/install-guide.rst'], 'message': 'Add nova scheduler_host_subset_size option to docs

This should be set higher than the number of nodes in the deployment,
because otherwise nova will continue to pick the same nodes as instances
cycle out, meaning some machines may never be used while others get many
instances provisioned.

This also helps with scheduler races when booting a large number of
instances at the same time.

Change-Id: I5a898616743105fe5410d7370a91e5c60120b596
'}]
commit_message:
Add nova scheduler_host_subset_size option to docs

This should be set higher than the number of nodes in the deployment,
because otherwise nova will continue to pick the same nodes as instances
cycle out, meaning some machines may never be used while others get many
instances provisioned.

This also helps with scheduler races when booting a large number of
instances at the same time.

Change-Id: I5a898616743105fe5410d7370a91e5c60120b596

commit_message:
Move barbican to authtoken

Create a new class to handle all configuration for
keystone_authtoken section in configuration file using
keystone::resource::authtoken

This patch is not backward compatible:
- we have change auth_type in api.pp to auth_strategy,
because auth_type is related to keystone authentication.
- removed all parameters related to keystone_authtoken
from api.pp and moved to authtoken.pp

Change-Id: I2dee8a3d1c399234941f96d8f21f49526777f501
Depends-On: I94914ed5a8b5c1447606547b31ed46bb72b4de01
Related-Bug: #1604463

commit_message:
Fix useless api_version of Manager class

Manager's api_version property is used by api_version.wraps. It
should not be an "empty" class and the real api_version can be
read from Client class.

Change-Id: Ib9dbd6d4243d94271b24177555193fcea27afcea

subject: Better control of mariadb restarts in upgrades
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2016-08-15 10:02:31.000000000', 'files': ['releasenotes/notes/mariadb-rolling-upgrades-323510425c3c7751.yaml', 'scripts/run-upgrade.sh', 'scripts/upgrade-utilities/playbooks/galera-cluster-rolling-restart.yml'], 'message': 'Better control of mariadb restarts in upgrades

This commit adds additional control around how the galera cluster
nodes are restarted during an upgrade (both the openstack upgrade
as well as mariadb upgrade). lxc config that gets added during the
lxc-container-create play would normally force a container restart.
This commit essentially does the following:

- run lxc-container-create on galera nodes but prevent container restarts
  from being triggered by the new lxc config that gets laid down
- run a mariadb upgrade
- run a controlled rolling restart of all mariadb cluster containers

(cherry picked from commit fd690e1fc3e9c90a0676e87ed8453b9dd33fe4c6)

Conflicts:
	scripts/run-upgrade.sh

Change-Id: I5d979eb15c471274cc14ce6f41c8ae479c5131d6
'}]
commit_message:
Better control of mariadb restarts in upgrades

This commit adds additional control around how the galera cluster
nodes are restarted during an upgrade (both the openstack upgrade
as well as mariadb upgrade). lxc config that gets added during the
lxc-container-create play would normally force a container restart.
This commit essentially does the following:

- run lxc-container-create on galera nodes but prevent container restarts
  from being triggered by the new lxc config that gets laid down
- run a mariadb upgrade
- run a controlled rolling restart of all mariadb cluster containers

(cherry picked from commit fd690e1fc3e9c90a0676e87ed8453b9dd33fe4c6)

Conflicts:
	scripts/run-upgrade.sh

Change-Id: I5d979eb15c471274cc14ce6f41c8ae479c5131d6

'}]
commit_message:
Move other-requirements.txt to bindep.txt

The default filename for documenting binary dependencies has been
changed from "other-requirements.txt" to "bindep.txt" with the release
of bindep 2.1.0. While the previous name is still supported, it will
be deprecated.

Move the file around to follow this change.

Note that this change is self-testing, the OpenStack CI infrastructure
will use a "bindep.txt" file to setup nodes for testing.

For more information about bindep, see also:
http://docs.openstack.org/infra/manual/drivers.html#package-requirements
http://docs.openstack.org/infra/bindep/

As well as this announcement:
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2016-August/101590.html

Change-Id: I3cf19cf423de4a65700a1eb30a2d8f43d64af278

commit_message:
Fix check_asserttruefalse syntax validator

According to Neutron developer documentation[1], it's better to use
assertTrue/False methods instead of generic assertEqual. The regex
created for check_asserttruefalse was skipping unit tests located on
test_netns_cleanup.py file.  This change includes those scenarios.

[1] http://docs.openstack.org/developer/neutron/devref/effective_neutron.html#mocking-and-testing

Change-Id: Id2eacf14d4b0740f3b044520074c7ab78768b319

commit_message:
Images api-ref: Redirect WADL docs to in-tree RST docs

The new RST-based, in-tree Images API Reference docs are ready
to take over for the old WADL-based docs.

The Images API Reference has been slightly restructured to pull
out the common /versions call and the /v2/metadefs API calls.
Thus the redirect for both the old v1 reference and the old
v2 reference redirect to the same place, that is, the "Image Service
APIs" landing page.

Change-Id: Iaf8ccbe1248b12e9e8fef48d52aeb7688fbac8a1

commit_message:
Add the upper constraints to package versions

Currently tox does not have any upper constraints, due to which there is a
possibility of tox to use a newer version of dependent library that may not

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-08-08 23:14:49.000000000', 'files': ['heat/engine/update.py', 'heat/common/exception.py', 'heat/engine/resource.py'], 'message': 'Alias UpdateReplace in its rightful location

A deeply misguided effort to move all exceptions out of the
heat.engine.resource module, where they belong, and into the
heat.common.exception module, where they largely do not, broke the API for
third-party resource plugins.

This change adds an alias in the correct location so that plugins
written against previous (and future) releases of Heat will continue to
work.

This reverts commit 4e2cfb991ada853023cd0994db2bf9a39126c538.

Change-Id: Iedd5d07d6c0c07e39e51a0fb810665b3e9c61f87

(cherry picked from commit c73874ad75c835b6b7b4a1ded5900fbcfc7103dc)
'}]
commit_message:
Alias UpdateReplace in its rightful location

A deeply misguided effort to move all exceptions out of the
heat.engine.resource module, where they belong, and into the
heat.common.exception module, where they largely do not, broke the API for
third-party resource plugins.

This change adds an alias in the correct location so that plugins
written against previous (and future) releases of Heat will continue to
work.

This reverts commit 4e2cfb991ada853023cd0994db2bf9a39126c538.

Change-Id: Iedd5d07d6c0c07e39e51a0fb810665b3e9c61f87
Closes-Bug: #1611104
(cherry picked from commit c73874ad75c835b6b7b4a1ded5900fbcfc7103dc)

commit_message:
Fixing RabbitMQ Defaults

This patch changes the default values for RabbitMQ servers,
SSL, and port to pull from the global values, rather than using
hardcoded values.  This preserves the original behavior while
allowing the user to specify service-specific settings if required.

Change-Id: Ic1ca9a1fa9d26c119ada938374de06ab49c11fe1

commit_message:
Move other-requirements.txt to bindep.txt

The default filename for documenting binary dependencies has been
changed from "other-requirements.txt" to "bindep.txt" with the release
of bindep 2.1.0. While the previous name is still supported, it will
be deprecated.

Move the file around to follow this change.

Note that this change is self-testing, the OpenStack CI infrastructure
will use a "bindep.txt" file to setup nodes for testing.

For more information about bindep, see also:
http://docs.openstack.org/infra/manual/drivers.html#package-requirements
http://docs.openstack.org/infra/bindep/

As well as this announcement:
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2016-August/101590.html

Change-Id: Ida04b2a6277f141701d20fe55ac327a1e8513adf

subject: Fix DHCP test scenario
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-08-09 20:50:29.000000000', 'files': ['playbooks/test-bifrost.yaml', 'playbooks/roles/bifrost-create-vm-nodes/files/create_vm_nodes-for-role.sh'], 'message': "Fix DHCP test scenario

It appears that test nodes, once are explicitly powered off,
depending on libvirt, may completely vanish. As we only test
at the end of the process if we've observed additional DHCP
leases, we should move to only defining the VMs such that they
are powered on when the sequence is ready, not in advance of
the test sequence.

Moving to defining instead of creating does improve the overall
efficency of the sequence as no processes are spawning suddenly
using CPU and RAM during the start of the test. This also allows
us to remove and correct ansible virt module invocations.

The ansible virt module is an extra module, not a core module,
at least on Ubuntu Trusty, cannot have it's requirements installed
via pip.

Change-Id: I8948ba5a941384fdcacebcdfe9b6fd4fe8384cb1
Depends-On: I01885c397ed1e020aae306db1656678b26306532
"}]
commit_message:
Fix DHCP test scenario

It appears that test nodes, once are explicitly powered off,
depending on libvirt, may completely vanish. As we only test
at the end of the process if we've observed additional DHCP
leases, we should move to only defining the VMs such that they
are powered on when the sequence is ready, not in advance of
the test sequence.

Moving to defining instead of creating does improve the overall
efficency of the sequence as no processes are spawning suddenly
using CPU and RAM during the start of the test. This also allows
us to remove and correct ansible virt module invocations.

The ansible virt module is an extra module, not a core module,
at least on Ubuntu Trusty, cannot have it's requirements installed
via pip.

Change-Id: I8948ba5a941384fdcacebcdfe9b6fd4fe8384cb1
Depends-On: I01885c397ed1e020aae306db1656678b26306532

commit_message:
For detection, treat libvirt vm_probation as int

Previously, when the libvirt detection plugin was called, vm_probation
would be written out as a string which would cause
the check plugin to fail. Now, vm_probation is converted to an
integer. If the conversion fails, a message is output and vm_probation
is set its default. This is consistent with the handling of the
other parameters to the libvirt detection plugin.

Fix nova_refresh as well

Change-Id: I77432a7200e2184d574ce125858853514d95a840
Closes-Bug: #1611905

commit_message:
increase novaclient functional timeout.

During current runs setting up the environment is taking long enough
that the tests are given only 24 minutes to run. This is very often
not long enough for the tests to complete. So we're getting failure
unrelated to code changes.

Move the job timeout from 70 minutes to 120 minutes to give us more
time.

Change-Id: I7060287c77b8a86c656464ee3f9cb5135eb3817e

commit_message:
Fix courtesy env-var file for recent auth changes

In the Newton cycle, Ironic receieved updates to the API code that
handles keystone interaction.  As such, the token appears to receive
basic validation even if it is invalid. This has broken our courtesy
env-vars helper file.

Changed the fake auth token such that the server side token
validation does not fail upon receieving a single space.

Change-Id: I44a4c931add0538fb60ba09ff02b130f3bf3fbf3

commit_message:
Revert "Do not call CPU&HugePages distributors"

Lack of testing was found, it's impossible to specify hugepages if
host supports only 2M huge pages due to incorrect validation.

This reverts commit 9bd61c68dc5cc05cdb8277e1f2e02c4a1a9a37aa.

Change-Id: I7945d165764608ca7ee8ac5f46463267718678f5
